

#calculate rotation angle
    Degrees per Pulse = Number of degrees in a circle/Number of encoder pulses per rotation
        Degrees per Pulse (DPP) : How many degrees per one pulse rotation.
        Number of degrees in a circle : 360 degrees.
        Number of encoder pulses per rotation (PPR): pulse number.

        e.g: For a 5000 line count incremental rotary encoder we divide 360 by 5000 to get
             0.072 degrees of rotation per pulse.
             

             °°°°°°°°°°°°°